# 11 Next.js + React Native Implementation Overlays

## Intent
Apply baseline controls consistently to rewrite targets: Next.js web and React Native Android.

## Next.js Overlay
- Enforce server-side authorization for all sensitive operations.
- Prevent sensitive data exposure through SSR caching, headers, and client bundles.
- Use CSRF/session protections for state-changing web requests.

## React Native Overlay
- Store tokens/secrets in secure OS-backed storage only.
- Avoid PHI/personal data in device logs, crash payloads, and analytics events.
- Require certificate pinning strategy and secure network configuration for production.

## Plugin Command Overlay
- Every plugin command/action must declare data access scope, purpose, and retention class.
- Plugin command execution must go through centralized policy enforcement and audit hooks.
- Disable plugin command execution when consent/policy prerequisites are not met.
